      "content": "wait, you're saying it's a \"resounding failure\"? that's a pretty strong take. i thought historians usually argue that while it can't stop everything, it's still the only way we have to keep countries talking. isn't it more like the UN is just limited by how much power individual countries actually want to give it? like, is the problem the UN itself, or is it just how the world works?",
